An Act pertaining to regional resilience and flood protection entities.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Chapter 21A of the General Laws, as printed in the 2022 Edition, is hereby amended by
2 inserting after Section 28 the following:
3 Section 29. There is hereby created and placed within the office of environmental affairs
4 a body politic and corporate and a public instrumentality to be known as the Massachusetts
5 Flood Management and Mitigation Authority, referred to in this section as the Authority, which
6 shall serve to coordinate flood management and mitigation efforts by local governments, tribal
7 authorities, regional planning bodies, watershed organizations and environmental nonprofits,
8 philanthropic organizations, and other entities.
9 (a) The Authority shall be an independent public authority not subject to the supervision
10 or control of the executive office of environmental affairs or of any other executive office,
